<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>100 Books</title>
    <!-- Le HTML5 shim, for IE6-8 support of HTML elements -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
      <script src="http://html5shim.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/html5.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
    <link rel="stylesheet/less" href="@Url.Content("~/bootstrap/less/bootstrap.less")"  />
    <link rel="stylesheet/less" href="@Url.Content("~/css/less/ohb.less")"  />
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/lib/less/less-1.3.0.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/lib/modernizr/modernizr.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/js/lib/jquery/jquery-1.7.1.js"></script>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/bootstrap/js/bootstrap-modal.js"></script>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="navbar">
        <div class="navbar-inner">
            <div class="container" id="menubar">
                <span class="brand">100 Books</span>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="hero-unit">
            <h1>@ViewBag.Title</h1>
            <p>You know those lists like _X books you must read before you die_? 100 Books helps you keep track what books you've read, what books you want to read next, and what your friends are reading.</p>
            <p><input type="button" id="fblogin" class="btn-large btn-primary pull-right" value="Login using Facebook" disabled="disabled" /></p>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="span4">
                <h4>Get inspired</h4>
                <p>Follow artists, writers and industry leaders to see what they're reading.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span4">
                <h4>Keep up</h4>
                <p>Follow your friends and see what they've been reading.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span4">
                <h4>Not sure what to read next?</h4>
                <p>Stick to reading lists and people you follow.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row">
            <div class="span4">
                <h4>Track what you've read</h4>
                <p>Show the world how well-read you are with your public profile.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span4">
                <h4>Master the classics</h4>
                <p>Where's that quote from? Work your way through the classics with specialised reading lists.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="span4">
                <h4>Expand your repertoire</h4>
                <p>There's some books everyone should read in a lifetime. Find them with 100 Books.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div id="fb-root">
        </div>
        <script>
            window.fbAsyncInit = function () {

                function facebooklogin() {
                    FB.init({
                        appId: '@Facebook.FacebookApplication.Current.AppId',
                        cookie: true,
                        xfbml: true,
                        oauth: true
                    });

                    FB.login(function (response) {
                        if (response.authResponse) {
                            // user authorized
                            window.location = '/Profile';
                        } else {
                            // user cancelled
                        }
                    }, { scope: '@ViewBag.ExtendedPermissions' });
                };

                $(function () {
                    // make the button is only enabled after the facebook js sdk has been loaded.
                    $('#fblogin').attr('disabled', false).click(facebooklogin);
                });
            };
            (function () {
                var e = document.createElement('script'); e.async = true;
                e.src = document.location.protocol + '//connect.facebook.net/en_US/all.js';
                document.getElementById('fb-root').appendChild(e);
            } ());
        </script>
    </div>
    <!-- /container -->
</body>
</html>
